## вљЎ What is this?

`xss-detect.zeek` hooks into Zeek's `http_request` event and checks the unescaped request URI against a large combined `pattern` covering tag-based, event-handler, JavaScript-sink, and encoded XSS payloads.

<br>

## рџЋЇ Detection Rule

<div align="center">

| # | Rule | Trigger | Severity |
|:---:|:---|:---|:---:|
| 1 | XSS Payload | HTTP request URI matches any XSS signature (see below) | рџџ  **HIGH** |

</div>

**Signatures covered** (all case-insensitive):

| Category | Patterns |
|:---|:---|
| Script tags | <code>&lt;script</code>, <code>&lt;/script&gt;</code>, <code>&lt; script</code> |
| Pseudo-protocols | `javascript:`, `vbscript:`, `data:text/html` |
| Event handlers | `onerror=`, `onload=`, `onclick=`, `onmouseover=`, `onmouseout=`, `onfocus=`, `onkeyup=`, `onchange=`, `onsubmit=`, `onunload=`, `onbeforeunload=` |
| Injectable tags | <code>&lt;img src&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;iframe&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;object&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;embed&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;applet&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;meta refresh&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;link href&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;style&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;form&gt;</code> |
| JS sinks | `document.cookie`, `document.location`, `document.write`, `document.domain`, `window.location`, `innerHTML`, `outerHTML` |
| JS functions | `alert(`, `prompt(`, `confirm(`, `eval(`, `expression(`, `String.fromCharCode` |
| Encoded variants | `%3Cscript`, `&#`, `\x3c`, `\u003c` |

<br>

## рџ“Љ Log Output

Alerts are written to **`xss_alerts.log`** (JSON). Fields:

<div align="center">

| Field | Description |
|:---|:---|
| `ts` | Timestamp of the request |
| `uid` | Zeek connection UID |
| `id` | Full connection 4-tuple (`id.orig_h`, `id.orig_p`, `id.resp_h`, `id.resp_p`) |
| `method` | HTTP method (GET, POST, etc.) |
| `payload` | The unescaped URI containing the matched XSS pattern |

</div>

<br>

## рџ”” Notice Type

| Notice | Fires When |
|:---|:---|
| `XSS_Attempt` | Request URI matches any signature in `xss_patterns` |

